- "glowing reviews" refers to positive review ratings given by guests;
- "number of times they have been visited" refers to the number of bookings for each property.

- 'Flowers blooming with high guest satisfaction' refers to properties with a high average rating;
- 'History of frequent bookings' refers to properties with a high number of confirmed bookings;
- 'Room to welcome new visitors' refers to properties that have at least one available day in the next 30 days.

- "shine the brightest" refers to properties with the highest average ratings;
- "stars in the sky" is a metaphor for the top properties;
- "inhabit" refers to the cities where the properties are located;
- "details of their hosts" include the host name and response time.

- "Crown of excellence" refers to the top 10 rankings;
- "Highest average guest ratings" is calculated by averaging the ratings given by guests;
- "Quickest host responses" refers to the host's response rate;
- "Grandest size" refers to the property size in square feet or meters;
- "Most available days" refers to the total number of days the property is available for booking.

